{"type":"message","id":"7cdddffd","parentId":"066a5d5c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:18:38.323Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_hqo9gc8o70k7_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 151714\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: experiment (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state and decide on the next concrete action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\r\n2. Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n3. CFI Compression Experiment completed - found that CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120) is the three-dimensional filter\r\n\r\nThe pending action is:\r\n- [ ] Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n  - Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n  - Test: does this distinguish \"constant format\" (freq≈160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)?\r\n  - Run: 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nThis is the most concrete next step. I should implement the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment. Let me look at the existing CFI compression synthesis document to understand the current state, then design and implement the hybrid experiment.\r\n\r\nThe key insight from the last session:\r\n- \"constant format\" tokens have freq≈160, CFI=1.0\r\n- \"research trajectory\" tokens have freq<120, CFI>0.5\r\n\r\nThe hybrid formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nThis would:\r\n- For constant format (CFI=1.0, freq=160): score = 1.0 × min(1, 160/120) = 1.0 × 1.0 = 1.0\r\n- For research trajectory (CFI=0.96, freq=136): score = 0.96 × min(1, 136/120) = 0.96 × 1.0 = 0.96\r\n\r\n\r\n- For medium-high freq (CFI=0.7, freq=80): score = 0.7 × min(1, 80/120) = 0.7 × 0.667 = 0.467\r\n\r\nI see the formula has a potential issue. At freq=160, the constant format still gets a score of 1.0, which means it hasn't effectively filtered out these tokens. I need to redesign the scoring mechanism to create a more nuanced separation between constant and research tokens.\r\n\r\nThe key problem is that the current scoring doesn't differentiate enough at high frequencies. I'll need to introduce a more sophisticated approach that penalizes extremely frequent tokens while maintaining the core CFI weighting.\r\n\r\nMy next step is to carefully examine the existing CFI implementation and pulse scripts to design a more intelligent scoring function that truly distinguishes token types.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI compression synthesis identified the constant-format problem but the three-dimensional filter (CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq < 120) is a binary threshold approach. The next pending experiment is implementing the hybrid scoring formula to test if it better distinguishes metaprogramming artifacts from research tokens.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nDesign and implement the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment by adding the scoring formula to the existing pulse analysis script. This requires updating the experiment infrastructure to compute `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` and compare its performance against binary thresholds.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: ## Pending\r\n- [ ] Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n  - Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n  - Test: does this distinguish \"constant format\" (freq≈160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)?\r\n  - Run: 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\r\n- [ ] Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\r\n- [ ] Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n- [ ] Design actual compression network (currently only analyzed text invariants)\r\nnew_text: - [ ] Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\r\n- [ ] Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n- [ ] Design actual compression network (currently only analyzed text invariants)\r\nfile: research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis clears the completed hybrid scoring experiment from pending once the experiment runs and validates the formula.\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:17:29\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774379918322}}
{"type":"message","id":"2062c651","parentId":"7cdddffd","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:18:45.864Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse ran successfully. Let me also check the log from the pulse that just ran. The new log file is `pulse_2026-03-24 151714.md` but that's the log from 15:17:14, which is the PREVIOUS pulse. The current pulse is the one I just triggered. Let me check if there's a newer log file from the pulse I just ran.\n\nWait, looking at the pulse output again - the observation mentions the CFI compression synthesis and that the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment is \"completed\". But looking at the context, this seems like the log file content from the PREVIOUS pulse (15:17:14). \n\nThe system timestamp shows 2026-03-24 15:17 UTC, which is 11:17 AM EDT, but the current time is 3:18 PM EDT. So the log file I'm looking at is from about 4 hours ago, not from the pulse I just triggered.\n\nLooking at the pulse output more carefully - the observation is about clearing a pending hybrid scoring experiment from the research document, but this seems to be documenting a mutation rather than actually performing it. The real action I need to take is implementing the CFI filtering and then wiring up the Breakaway pulses to the actual TemporalAttention backend.","thinkingSignature":"85354b2d11d74b96f5568c8bdf3a108668c96bf294e9a9e3e0d72a85eab5c745"},{"type":"text","text":"Now let me check the most recent log file to see what happened in this pulse cycle:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cl5t1sq3yjng_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\" -File | Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | Select-Object -First 1 | ForEach-Object { $_.FullName }"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1486,"output":359,"cacheRead":12245,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14090,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheR